    "body": "## Purpose\n\nFixes #34477\n\n- Add missing `None→0` guard for `num_expert_group` in `flashinfer_fused_moe_blockscale_fp8`, matching the pattern already used for `topk_group` on the next line and in the sister function `fi_trtllm_fp8_per_tensor_moe`\n- Add regression test covering `num_expert_group=None` with `DeepSeekV3` routing on the block-scale FP8 path\n\n**Root cause**: MiniMax-M2.1 uses `scoring_func=\"sigmoid\"` with `e_score_correction_bias` but does not use grouped top-k routing, so `num_expert_group` defaults to `None`. When DeepSeekV3 routing is selected on GB200 with FP8 block-scale quantization, the `None` is passed directly to the flashinfer kernel (which interprets it as 0), triggering:\n```\nTVM_FFI_ICHECK(args->n_group != 0) << \"n_group should not be zero for DeepSeekV3 routing\"\n```\n\n## Test Plan\n\nAdd new test case `pytest tests/kernels/moe/test_flashinfer.py::test_flashinfer_blockscale_fp8_none_expert_group` (requires Blackwell GPU)\n\n",
    "created_at": "2026-02-13T05:56:28Z",
